## How To Use
1. Record reliable monthly income.  
2. Capture committed fixed obligations first.  
3. Estimate day-to-day variable spend honestly.  
4. Allocate savings and financial goals.  
5. Review the resulting position and adjust behaviour where needed.

The value comes from consistency and regular review.

---

## Core Budgeting Principles

### 1) Plan Before Spending
Money should have direction.

### 2) Be Realistic
Over-optimistic assumptions break budgets.

### 3) Track Trends
Patterns reveal opportunities to improve.

### 4) Review Monthly
Control improves with repetition.

